		   <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top">Grouping your SK, the first 30 levels<br clear=all>
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Fri, Aug 25th 5:27 PM2000 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/db/classes.html?class=5&mid=96723885923619&post=1"><a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=5&mid=96723885923619&num=0&post=1&replyto=96723885923619"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=96723885923619></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=375"><span id=Scholar>Andari</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>54 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.50]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Andari&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;   Hello again all, Andari here with another post on how to run your SK in groups.And where I found was best to go and get those groups.<br><br>Levels 1 to 9<br>     At these levels you shouldn't bother wasting your time to group, as your sk abilities,hps,and ac should be more than enough to match up against any even or blue monster.There are many different creatures to fight at these levels..finding some should be no problem.If you decide(against my advice) to group..get a cleric :)<br><br>Levels 9 to 12<br>     Alright you have finally come into your own as a SK finally, by getting some spells.The best places I found to fight(this is pre-kunark btw) were in the orc camps of east commons, or in befallen.Try to make sure the group has atleast 1 cleric and/or bard for healing, because you will absorb alot of damage due to aggroing mobs.(At these levels I out damaged warriors and monks of the same levels with pure damage and spells.)A nuker of some sort is always nice.If you choose befallen, make sure your party has a cleric, and maybe a paladin too.<br><br>Levels 12 to 17<br>     Now is when the fun really starts..many different zones become accesable and viable.You can goto NRO and get into a derv group;Oasis and hunt spiders,caimen,crocs,orcs;West Commons and hunt dervs;Befallen is still decent;Highhold pass against gnolls and orcs;Najena and hunt skeletons and ogre guards;or SRO and hunt dervs.<br>     Remember that any place you choose, try to make sure you have some kind of healer in the group.At 15 you should become the groups puller with your clinging darkness spell, generally that and a siphon strength will keep the mob aggroed on you during the battle,as you should by now have a respectable (damage-wise) weapon.<br><br>Levels 17 to 22<br>     At these levels you can now go off to lake rathe to get yourself a group killing av guards.This will be the best exp you'll find.You can also get in a group and kill Aviaks in sk, or (if you are lucky) get into a treant group in SK.<br><br>Levels 22 to 30<br>     There is literally a bunch of places to go at these levels.In the early stages of this group, you can hunt in unrest,Mistmoore,najena, UGuk,OOT for the named dwarves and sisters,Rathe mts against preservers and giant skels, and in SK against Aviak harriers and avocets.Later the best grouping will by far be in Cazic Thule: the home of our decaying armor pieces for our quest armor.<br><br>Level 30 and beyond..<br>     While I haven't gotten here yet, I know from others in my guild a somewhat sketchy idea of the best spots,as follows:<br>level 30 to 35..stay in cazic,complete your       darkforge collection of armor.<br>level 35 to 40..get in groups slaying sg's in sro or oasis, also spectre groups in oot and oasis.Deep water Goblins are also good from what I hear..<br>level 40 to 50..go to Lguk, get in any group(especially frenzy room for fssb) and kill.kill.kill..<br>level 50 to ????..I haven't heard to much from these but..I have heard that planar raids, and the hole can be very good..<br><br>   A thought on group make up for you...the best groups I worked with had a very good mix, me(the sk) a pally,a cleric, a wiz,an enc, and druid/ranger being usually the best mix. I've also had some cool groups with rogues(best in pairs..rogue ping-pong :)..and bards, if they know what they are doing.By far and away the most important member for you to group will be to have a healer of some sort(clr/dru/shm), and having another back up healer (pally/rng..or dru/shm if you have clr) will be very helpful.In most groups the sk is the puller, so expect to take damage..just remember to keep casting and taunting, and let the healer handle his part.<br><br>well that's all for now..till next time ;)<br><br>Andari D'Belladona<br>26 Tier'Dal Shadow Knight<br>Fennin Ro<br><br>feel free to look me up :)</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Crusaders of Drunken Might<br><br>&#8220;You are all just jealous because the voices choose to talk to m</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td class=mhback align=right><span class=mh id=fs8><a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=5><img src=/shared/root_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Up" width=17 height=11> Thread Index</a> |  <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=5&post=1><img src=/shared/new_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="New" width=17 height=11> New Subject</a> | <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=5&mid=96723885923619&num=0&post=1&mid=96723885923619><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply" width=17 height=11> Reply to Thread</a></span></td></tr><tr><td><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="mform"><tr><td id="fs8">0 Posts [ <a href="/fsearch.html?base=class5">Search Forums</a> ]</nobr></td></tr></table>&nbsp;</td></tr>
